&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess an active TS/SCI security clearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in project management, acquisition management, or another related discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of relevant work experience related to project/program management and full life-cycle acquisition management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong acquisition experience and an understanding of DoW acquisition decision-making processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the DoD Planning, Programming Budgeting and Execution Process, budgetary principles, and their associated operational impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Program Management Practitioner certification through the Defense Acquisition Workforce Improvement Act (DAWIA) “Back to Basics” certification framework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with, briefing, and engaging General Officer/Flag Officer/SES-level personnel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead disparate teams and build coalitions within a community of interest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel to meetings in the National Capitol Region and occasional CONUS travel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chemical and/or biological defense work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DAWIA Program Management Advanced certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management Professional (PMP) certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Individual salaries are

