&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess an active TS/SCI security clearance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in biology, chemistry, or a related field is required. Master’s degree equivalent to 3 years’ worth of experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience as an Action Officer, staff officer, in acquisitions, military medicine, AI activities, or similar related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with the oversight of acquisition programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced degree in a relevant field of study&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of DoW Artificial Intelligence applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with the oversight of medical countermeasure programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading or managing relevant medical projects or programs for a DoW agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) approval process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior programming and budgeting and program management experience&lt;/li&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;ANSER enhances national and homeland security by strengthening public institutions. We provide thought leadership for complex issues through independent analysis, and we deliver practical, useful solutions. ANSER values collaboration, integrity, and initiative and we are client focused in all that we do. Because we were established for the purpose of public service and not for profit, we measure our success in the impact of our service.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ANSER is seeking a Cloud Engineer to support cloud infrastructure, interoperability, and cybersecurity operations for government biometric systems and enterprise cloud environments. In this role, you will provide cloud application operations, maintenance, and enhancement support while enabling secure data sharing between DoD and interagency biometric systems. You will support cloud architecture development, cybersecurity compliance, RMF activities, vulnerability management, and Cloud Security Service Provider (CSSP) integration efforts. You will also assist with cloud-based biometric system integration, user training, and implementation of secure, scalable cloud solutions supporting mission-critical operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day-to-Day Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide infrastructure and cloud engineering support to enable interoperability between government biometric systems and cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support cloud application operations, maintenance, upgrades, and continual enhancement activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement, monitor, and audit security controls to ensure compliance with government cybersecurity standards and RMF requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with obtaining and supporting Cloud Security Service Provider (CSSP) capabilities for cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate RMF documentation and cybersecurity artifacts to support system authorization and compliance activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform vulnerability scans, IAVM monitoring, and remediation activities across cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development of cloud architectures integrating biometric systems including BAT-A, NRTIO, and NXGBCC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define end-to-end cloud architecture and system boundary documentation required for Army CIO RMF approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with vulnerability testing, compliance validation, and cybersecurity assessments for BPS cloud architecture environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide user training and operational support for cloud-hosted applications and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Secret Clearance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in a relevant technical discipline, will consider additional two (2) years of relevant experience in lieu of a degree.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of six (6) years of experience in cloud engineering, DevOps, or cloud security role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional-level certification such as AWS Certified Security – Specialty, Azure Security Engineer, CISSP, or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with AWS or Azure cloud environments, with preference for AWS GovCloud or Azure Government experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of cloud networking principles, including VPCs, subnets, routing, VPNs, and hybrid cloud connectivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting RMF compliance activities, vulnerability scanning, and cybersecurity monitoring in cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience implementing and maintaining cloud security controls in compliance with government or DoD standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with cybersecurity tools and processe

