&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Top Secret with SCI eligibility security clearance required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 years of Force Protection, Mission Assurance and physical security experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of national-level agency security processes, procedures, and requirements, including Defense Critical Infrastructure DCI, Task Critical Assts (TCA), Critical Asset Protection (CAP) and Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI) standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of clearance processing, physical security, and document control functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency Management background in Force Protection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facility Security Officer certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing Sensitive Compartmented Information Facilities (SCIFs) operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with databases, such as National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST), National Industrial Security System (NISS), and Defense Information System for Security (DISS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Mission Assurance Risk Management Systems (MARMS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
