&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in engineering (civil, structural, mechanical, or electrical), construction management, or related discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a Contracting Officer’s Representative (COR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 7 years’ experience in military construction (MILCON) program management, including troop labor, UMMC, and related areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated expertise in engineering design and construction project management, including scheduling, cost control, cost estimating, construction management, quality assurance, and budget management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong contracting skills, including pre-award tasks, RFP development, contract award procedures, and post-award contract management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough understanding of contract types: design-build (DB), design-bid-build (DBB), firm-fixed-price (FFP), and cost-plus (CP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with, or employment by, a Department of Defense (DoD) Design and Construction Agent (DCA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to coordinate across multiple agencies and stakeholders in a complex, joint operational environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s degree in engineering, construction management, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PMP or similar project management certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with posture infrastructure programs in the Indo-Pacific region.&lt;/li&gt;
